python-decorator: python-decorator (Module to simplify usage of decorators)
python-decorator:
python-decorator: The aim of the decorator module is to simplify the usage of decorators
python-decorator: for the average programmer, and to popularize decorators usage giving
python-decorator: examples of useful decorators, such as memoize, tracing,
python-decorator: redirecting_stdout, locked, etc.  The core of this module is a
python-decorator: decorator factory called decorator.
